The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs and metric spaces, which are central topics in computer science. The use of linear programming relaxations and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The study of integrality gaps and the connection to Goddyn's conjecture suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the use of LP relaxations and approximation algorithms is a common theme in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
